laboratory_examinations.findings: Gallbladder is distended and contains several peripherally calcified gallstones, none of which appear to be impacted within the gallbladder neck. A sliver of fluid or gallbladder wall edema is seen along the liver margin. The liver enhances normally without focal concerning lesion. No intrahepatic biliary ductal dilation. The common bile duct appears normal in caliber. Pancreas appears normal without ductal dilation or signs of acute inflammation. Spleen is normal in size without focal lesion. Kidneys enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast promptly without hydronephrosis. No perinephric abnormality is seen. Stomach is mostly decompressed, and the duodenum is normal. No signs of ileus or obstruction in the loops of small bowel.
